.TH SFTPFS 4
.SH NAME
sftpfs \- sftp file server client
.SH SYNOPSIS
mount {
.B sftpfs
[
.B -dD
] [
.B -s
.I sshcmd
|
.I addr
]
}
mtpt
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Sftpfs
translates between styx messages and sftp (version 3) messages.  If
.I addr
is specified,
.IR ssh (1)
is executed to connect to the address request the sftp subsystem.
Otherwise
.I sshcmd
specified with
.B -s
is executed.
Option
.B -d
causes debug messages to be printed.
Option
.B -D
causes styx traces to be printed.
.SH EXAMPLE
Mount files from ``dis'':
.EX
	mount -c {sftpfs dis} /n/dis
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR mount (1),
.IR ssh (1).
.IR 
.SH SOURCE
.B /appl/cmd/sftpfs.b
.SH BUGS
See the ``todo'' section in the README for now.
